# Checkout must be LF everywhere — the repo is authored LF-only and the
# byte-hygiene gate (packages/shared test/repo-byte-hygiene.test.ts) forbids
# raw CR bytes, so a CRLF checkout on a Windows runner would flag every line.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shared work ledgers are append-heavy and written by concurrent
# loops/worktrees — union merge keeps both sides' additions instead of
# conflicting on every parallel append (the observed daily pain). Known
# tradeoff: simultaneous edits of the SAME line can duplicate instead of
# conflict — the ledgers' curation rule (prune on every write) absorbs it.
docs/goals/backlog.md merge=union
docs/goals/growth-backlog.md merge=union
docs/goals/rival-watch.md merge=union
